                <h2>Key Changes This Week: Surge in AI Copy Homogenization Complaints</h2>
<p>This week, we received feedback from multiple advertisers: <strong>AI-generated ad copies showed significantly declining CTR (click-through rates) after 3-5 days of投放</strong>, with some materials' CPM (cost per thousand impressions) rising over 20%.</p>
<p>In-depth analysis revealed the core issue: current mainstream AI copywriting tools have highly overlapping training data, causing massive advertisers to produce almost identical "hook phrases."</p>
<p>Typical manifestations include:<br />
- Openings always use "Are you still struggling with XX?"<br />
- Middle sections标配"99% of people don't know about XX"<br />
- Endings fixed as "Limited-time offer, click now"</p>
<p><strong>While such copy might have been effective in early 2023, against the backdrop of users encountering over 1,000 ads daily, it has become mere "noise."</strong></p>
<hr />
<h2>Deeper Impacts of Homogenization</h2>
<p>Homogenization isn't just about conversion efficiency—it affects brand asset accumulation.</p>
<p><strong>1. Declining Brand Recognition</strong></p>
<p>When all competitors use similar messaging, users struggle to remember "who's speaking." Take a utility app as an example: its AI-generated "Say goodbye to XX anxiety" copy shared over 70% similarity with competitors, causing brand search volume to decline instead of rise.</p>
<p><strong>2. Platform Traffic Distribution Limited</strong></p>
<p>ML systems on platforms like Meta and TikTok identify "creative fatigue" and actively reduce display frequency for similar materials. Even with higher bids, homogenized materials face systematic "punishment" in exposure volume.</p>
<p><strong>3. Shortened Material Lifecycles</strong></p>
<p>Materials that originally ran for 2 weeks now often need replacement within 5-7 days. This directly increases material production costs and account operational pressure.</p>
<hr />
<h2>3 Actionable Breakthrough Strategies</h2>
<h3>Strategy 1: Introduce "Anti-Pattern" Writing</h3>
<p>Proactively avoid AI's惯性 expressions:<br />
- Don't start with questions; use statements or scene descriptions instead<br />
- Avoid exaggerated numbers; use category specifics or emotional details<br />
- Drop urgency words like "now" or "limited time"; use "invite" or "experience" for lower pressure</p>
<p><strong>A home goods overseas team tested and found that abandoning "limited-time special" urgency messaging resulted in slightly lower CTR but 12% higher conversion rate, because attracted users had shorter decision cycles.</strong></p>
<h3>Strategy 2: Build Team-Exclusive "Copy Asset Library"</h3>
<p>Instead of generating from scratch each time, establish your team's validated copy template library.</p>
<p>Approach:<br />
1. Extract 3-5 high-performance phrases from top-performing materials weekly<br />
2. Categorize by industry,投放platform, user persona<br />
3. Use as "style anchors" for AI generation, guiding tools toward more differentiated content</p>
<p>This method preserves AI efficiency while avoiding "collision" with all online AI copy.</p>
<h3>Strategy 3: Move "Human Intervention Points" Forward in Human-AI Collaboration</h3>
<p>Most teams' approach: AI generates → Human reviews → Modifies and publishes.</p>
<p><strong>More effective approach: Humans provide "creative skeleton" first, then AI fills details.</strong></p>
<p>For example:<br />
- Humans determine core selling points, emotional tone, narrative rhythm<br />
- AI handles multi-version expansion and tone adjustment<br />
- Humans select optimal solution from multiple versions</p>
<p>This produces copy with both human judgment's uniqueness and AI's efficiency support.</p>
<hr />
<h2>This Week's Recommendations</h2>
<p>If you're troubled by AI copy homogenization, prioritize starting with <strong>"Anti-Pattern Writing"</strong>—the lowest-cost, fastest-results adjustment direction. Specific action: This week, have all AI-generated copy drafts reviewed against a "common hook list," proactively replace high-frequency phrases, then enter A/B testing.</p>
<p>Next week we'll continue tracking AI advertising material technology iterations. Stay tuned.</p>
